korosh_afshar@... wrote:

&gt; I have a TestCase in which I define a suite method so that I may do a
&gt; one time setup for all the tests within that  that TestCase. Lets say
&gt; TestCaseA
&gt;
&gt; I have some other TestCases (none have a single setup like above)
&gt; defined as well. Lets call it TestCaseB, TestCaseC.
&gt;
&gt; I have an AllTest object to test alll of the above.
&gt;
&gt; It seems that as soon as I add the TestCase with the single setup
&gt; schecme (TestCaseA), to my AllTest, the TestCase.suite() which does
&gt; the single time setup never gets called and subsequently my TestCaseA
&gt; with the suite method fails.
&gt;
&gt; All the other TestCases (TestCaseB, TestCaseC) work alright with the
&gt; AllTest.suite().
&gt;

Are you defining the TestCaseA.suite() method similar to the following?

    public static Test suite() {
        TestSuite suite = new TestSuite(TestCaseA.class);

        TestSetup oneTimer = new TestSetup(suite) {
            public void setUp() {
                oneTimeSetUp();
            }
        };

        return oneTimer;
    }

And the AllTests.suite() method similar to the following?

    public static Test suite() {
        TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();

        suite.addTest(TestCaseA.suite());
        suite.addTest(TestCaseB.suite());
        suite.addTest(TestCaseC.suite());

        return suite;
    }

